                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A woodblock printed guide to living a long and healthy life written by Kaibara Ekiken (1630-1714) in his eighties and published in 1713, the year before his death. In his view the route to a long life lay in a healthy lifestyle and morally upright conduct, and his advice includes self-restraint in matters of food, drink, sleep and sexual behaviour. </summary>

